<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-74-0932 </DOCNO><TEXT>On Monday 14 November, 1988, Sir Robert Haslam, Chairman, British CoalCorporation, held a press conference, during which he revealed 'outstanding'financial and technological performances. In reviewing the challengesand prospects, Sir Robert indicated that an operating profit of 190 millionpounds in the first half of the current year 1988/89 is British Coal'sbest financial performance for at least 20 years. It is 86 million poundsbetter than the first six months of last year and only just below theoperating profit achieved in the whole year. 1 tab.</TEXT></DOC>